nl.tue.fingerpaint.client.gui

Class GraphVisualisator

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tue.fingerpaint.client.gui.GraphVisualisator

  • public class GraphVisualisator
extends Object

    Class for the creation of segregation graphs.

    How to call this class

    Load the visualisation API, passing the onLoadCallback to be called when loading is done. This should be done as follows: 

       GraphVisualisator gv = new GraphVisualisator();
   Runnable onLoad = gv.createGraph(...);
   VisualizationUtils.loadVisualizationApi(onLoad, LineChart.PACKAGE);

    Author:
    Group Fingerpaint
